  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 180°C.",
    "Butter a baking dish of 18cm in diameter.",
    "In a pan, heat the olive oil and cook the sliced onion until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for another minute.",
    "Add the chopped parsley and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Stir in the Monterey Jack cheese until melted and well combined with the onion mixture.",
    "Pour in the Burgundy wine and stir well.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Transfer the mixture to the prepared baking dish and dot the top with butter.",
    "Bake in the preheated oven for 20 minutes, or until golden brown and bubbly.",
    "Serve immediately, garnished with additional parsley if desired."
